        <TableRow/>
      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>This example shows how to open a window.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22">Example
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>A window is opened by instantiating Window and calling the Show method. <Run FontWeight="Bold">Show</Run>
 opens a window and returns immediately without waiting for the new window to close. This type of window is also known as a <Run FontStyle="italic">modeless</Run>
 window, and doesn't restrict user input.
    </Paragraph>

    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>C# </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph xml:space="preserve" TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New"><Run>NewWindow newWindow = new NewWindow(); 
newWindow.Show(); 
// Returns immediately </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22">Security
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>Instantiating <Run FontWeight="Bold">Window</Run>
 requires permission to call unsafe native methods (see Window).
    </Paragraph>

